						<summary>

						<p>On the wall of the Veṅkateśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1760 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It states that Mudugala Bhīmarao, the carpenter along with Gautama-gowḍa of Kallūra grāma prepared the chariot of the temple and got exemption from the payment of the tax birāḍa. Probably, the seṭṭis (merchants) of the place made this exemption.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1682, Vikrama, Adhikaśrāvana ba. 3, Thursday corresponding to 1760 A.D., July 30. The week day was Wednesday.</p>						

						</summary>
